  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Health Services Policy Implementation Agent Dispatcher\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Health Services Policy Implementation Agent Dispatcher\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Health Services domain machine for policy implementation that dispatches AI agents for documentation, outreach, or partner coordination. It operationalizes the PH system transformation evaluation-plan workflow by watching evaluability, logic-model outputs, evaluation questions, selected measures, and AI-dispatchable intervention status. Output at [1795:1799] can trigger downstream agents or peer machines in the Policy Implementation pathway.\n\nPOPULATION: Community health service recipients, public health agencies, care partners, and cross-sector service networks\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- evaluability_readiness_norm (index 0):  0.0 = no usable data, support, or capacity; | 0.5 = partial evaluability; | 1.0 = clear scope, data, resources, and interest-holder support\n- service_delivery_pressure_norm (index 1):  0.0 = acute unmet demand or failed handoffs; | 0.5 = manageable pressure; | 1.0 = stable delivery capacity\n- equity_signal_norm (index 2):  0.0 = large disparity or excluded population; | 0.5 = known gap under mitigation; | 1.0 = equitable reach and experience\n- measure_confidence_norm (index 3):  0.0 = missing/low-quality measures; | 0.5 = partial indicator confidence; | 1.0 = timely, actionable, trusted measures\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- hsph-057-urgent-dispatch (RED) -> action: Dispatch care_coordinator_agent to resolve policy implementation delivery risk and update the evaluation plan matrix.\n- hsph-057-optimize-delivery (GREEN) -> action: Trigger optimization agent workflow for policy implementation using current logic-model outputs and measures.\n- hsph-057-stable-ideal-state (GREEN) -> action: Record sustained progress toward the ideal state for policy implementation and keep monitoring.",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "evaluability_readiness_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "no usable data, support, or capacity;",
          "mid": "partial evaluability;",
          "high": "clear scope, data, resources, and interest-holder support"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "service_delivery_pressure_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "acute unmet demand or failed handoffs;",
          "mid": "manageable pressure;",
          "high": "stable delivery capacity"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "equity_signal_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "large disparity or excluded population;",
          "mid": "known gap under mitigation;",
          "high": "equitable reach and experience"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "measure_confidence_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "missing/low-quality measures;",
          "mid": "partial indicator confidence;",
          "high": "timely, actionable, trusted measures"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "hsph-057-urgent-dispatch",
        "label": "hsph-057-urgent-dispatch",
        "rag": "RED",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "Dispatch care_coordinator_agent to resolve policy implementation delivery risk and update the evaluation plan matrix."
      },
